TO deploy using code deploy

Start with these steps:

Step 1 → Add appspec.yml to repo
Step 2 → Add scripts/deploy.sh to repo
Step 3 → Update buildspec.yml
Step 4 → Create CodeDeploy application
Step 5 → Create deployment group
Step 6 → Install CodeDeploy agent on EC2
Step 7 → Update pipeline add deploy stage
--------------------------------
Now update CodePipeline — add Deploy stage:
-------------------------------
Go to CodePipeline
Click → your pipeline (aws-pipeline)
Click → Edit
        │
        ▼
Click → Add Stage
        after Build stage

Stage name → Deploy
        │
        ▼
Add action group:
Action name    → DeployToEKS
Action provider→ AWS CodeDeploy
Input artifact → BuildArtifact
Application    → create new (next step)
Deployment group → create new (next step)
--------------------------------

Create CodeDeploy Application:
--------------------------
Go to CodeDeploy Console
Click → Create application

Application name → aws-pipeline-app
Compute platform → EC2/On-premises
                   ↑
                   for EKS we use this
                   with our deploy script
Click → Create application
-------------------------------------------------

Create Deployment Group:
------------------------

Click → Create deployment group

Group name      → eks-deployment-group
Service role    → create new role with CodeDeploy permissions
Deployment type → In-place
Environment     → EC2 instances
                  Tag: Name = codedeploy-agent-server

Deployment settings → CodeDeployDefault.AllAtOnce
Load balancer       → uncheck
Click → Create deployment group
--

Important note:

CodeDeploy for EKS needs
an EC2 instance with:
├── CodeDeploy agent installed
├── kubectl installed
├── AWS CLI installed
└── Access to EKS cluster

This EC2 acts as deployment runner
---------

Install CodeDeploy agent on EC2:

# SSH into EC2
sudo yum update -y
sudo yum install ruby wget -y

# Download agent
wget https://aws-codedeploy-us-east-2.s3.amazonaws.com/latest/install
chmod +x install
sudo ./install auto

# Start agent
sudo systemctl start codedeploy-agent
sudo systemctl enable codedeploy-agent

# Verify
sudo systemctl status codedeploy-agent
