------------------------------------
code build use its own linux to do the job right why code deploy not using like that?

CodeBuild — has its own environment:

CodeBuild:
→ AWS spins up fresh container
→ runs your buildspec.yml
→ container destroyed after build
→ no server needed ✅

You don't manage anything
AWS handles the environment

----

CodeDeploy — works differently:

CodeDeploy:
→ does NOT have its own environment
→ needs a TARGET to deploy TO
→ it just coordinates the deployment

CodeDeploy is a COORDINATOR
not an EXECUTOR like CodeBuild

What CodeDeploy needs as target:

Target options:
├── EC2 instances    ✅ most common
├── On-premises      ✅
├── ECS              ✅ native support
├── Lambda           ✅ native support
└── EKS              ❌ not native
                        that is why we need EC2
                        with kubectl

Why ECS works but EKS does not:

ECS + CodeDeploy:
→ AWS made them work together
→ native integration ✅
→ no extra setup needed

EKS + CodeDeploy:
→ no native integration ❌
→ need workaround
→ use EC2 with CodeDeploy agent
→ agent runs kubectl commands
----------------------------------------------------------------------
You need to tell CodeDeploy which EC2 to deploy to using Tags.

Not automatic — you specify using Tags:

CodeDeploy does NOT
automatically pick any EC2

You tell it:
"deploy to EC2 instances
 that have this tag"

----

Step 1 — Tag your EC2 instance:

Go to EC2 Console
Click your instance
Tags tab
Add tag:
Key   → Name
Value → codedeploy-server

--

Step 2 — Deployment Group uses that tag:

CodeDeploy
→ Create Deployment Group
→ Environment configuration
→ EC2 instances
→ Tag group:
   Key   → Name
   Value → codedeploy-server
           ↑
           CodeDeploy finds EC2
           with this tag
           and deploys there
------------
Visual:

CodeDeploy Deployment Group
        │
        │ looks for tag
        │ Name = codedeploy-server
        ▼
Finds matching EC2 instances:
├── EC2-1 (Name=codedeploy-server) ✅ deploy here
├── EC2-2 (Name=web-server)        ❌ skip
└── EC2-3 (Name=codedeploy-server) ✅ deploy here

---

Multiple servers same tag:

10 EC2 instances all tagged:
Name = codedeploy-server
        │
        ▼
CodeDeploy deploys to ALL 10
automatically ✅

No need to mention each server
Just use same tag ✅
